Business Brief -- Sony Corp.:
   Executive Accuses Company
   In Suit Alleging Racial Bias
Mr. Bermingham, 47 years old, is also asking for $40
million in damages from his boss, Shinichi Takagi, president
of Sony Recording Media of America.
   Mr. Bermingham, contends the company removed him as
president of domestic sales and marketing for Sony Magnetic
Products Group to show employees that "no Caucasian was
invulnerable."
   The lawsuit was called absurd by Jason Farrow, senior vice
president of corporate communications for Sony Corp. of
America, based in Park Ridge, N.J.